<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="814" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d814">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/10–1146: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-11T18:00:00-05:00">October
                                    11, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1822. Dept understands Stanvac<note n="25" xml:id="d814fn25">Standard–Vacuum Oil Company.</note> suggesting Shanghai office
                            attempt arrange for import <hi rend="italic">Balch</hi> cargo<note n="26" xml:id="d814fn26">Cargo aboard S.S. <hi rend="italic">Allen
                                    C. Balch</hi>.</note> in bond pending decision matters at issue
                            (your 1929 [bis], Oct 7). Dept feels import in bond if authorized would
                            represent reasonable ad interim compromise present impasse and
                            authorizes ConGen to support Stanvac’s representations in foregoing
                            sense.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>